`,i(e.p,{children:'Under these conditions, it was crucial prioritize what are 100% required tasks to be done, and what are the "nice-to-haves" left over.'}),`
`,i(e.h4,{children:"priority 1: rigging"}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"Rigging was top priority, no matter how unpolished the designs may be, if they can't be controlled, we don't have an event to show. So that was the first thing that I worked on implementing."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"Although animations were not being worked on, I made sure to bookmark the components that would need to be animated later whenever I knew I would need it. That way I was able to save myself a couple of hours once it was time to actually put the animations in!"}),`
`,i(e.h4,{children:"priority 2: polish"}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"Once rigging was completed, and all of the bugs were ironed out, I knew next priority was polishing the designs, it made no sense to set up all of the layout transitions if the designs were to be restructured anyway! And to be honest, I couldn't let myself allow these graphics to remain untouched."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"This step was the one that took much longer than expected, as I ran into a lot of design issues and it was difficult to try to keep as much faithful to the original vision, while ensuring that it was feasible."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:"One of the biggest challenges in this step was implementing all of the parts that were not part of the original design specification. For example the leaderboard, or how the maplist should show completed games."}),`
`,i(e.p,{children:i(e.img,{src:"/cg-fabl_6.gif",alt:"Here's a before/after of the roster screen! This gif was probably the most complex thing I've made with ffmpeg."})}),`
